= 3, 
otherwise they are our non-iterative baselines. The name of the training dataset is indicated below the word "Ours". 
"C+L" stands for COCO+LVIS.

Table 7. We notice that even the proposed baseline model with HR-
Net18+OCR backbone outperforms all previous methods. The proposed iterative method that uses a mask from the 
previous click sets a new state-of-the-art in interactive segmentation on all five benchmarks. Another notable fact 
is that the smallest among the proposed models with HRNet18s+OCR backbone performs on par with heavier ones, 
making it possible to use the proposed method on devices with low computational capability.
